  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "1",
      "body": "Cut Your Wood\n\n**Tip:** Cut to the following dimensions: (2) 2x2 at 10 ½” long (for benchtop end pieces) (5) 2x2 at 36” long (for benchtop slats)",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/e54443ec5d596fe5.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "2",
      "body": "Drill Pocket Holes\n\n**Tip:** Drill 2 pocket holes at each end of your 36” long 2x2 boards",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/59173c2a904fda59.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "3",
      "body": "Sand\n\n**Tip:** Sand edges and ends smooth."
    },
    {
      "title": "4",
      "body": "Attach Slats to End Pieces\n\n**Tip:** Using 2 ½” pocket hole screws, attach your 36” long 2x2 boards perpendicular to your 10 ½” long end pieces. Use a scrap 1x2 board turned on its side as a spacer between each slat.",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/2cb8e05a8127714f.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "5",
      "body": "Stain or Paint\n\n**Tip:** Stain your benchtop (I used special walnut stain), and you can also spray paint your hairpin legs (optional).",
      "image": "https://pub-b845b7e7b4924e4d8f2520661b54734d.r2.dev/plans/bf076e0716414257.webp"
    },
    {
      "title": "6",
      "body": "Attach Legs\n\n**Tip:** Attach your hairpin legs (I spaced mine 2 ½” in from each end)"
    }
  ],
